Rating: 3
Converted to lower fat/lower sugar. Delicious and berries did not sink! Used 1/3 C. sugar, 1/2 cup Splenda & added 1/2 tsp. baking soda to Splenda; used 3 TBS. water, 3 tsp. cornstarch; 12 oz. frozen blueberries; 4 egg whites, 1/2 c buttermilk; 1/4 c butter, 1/4 cup low fat sour cream. I added a generous helping of cinnamon/nutmeg to the batter to add to the flavor. I also used a slotted spoon to spoon berries onto the batter so all the liquid was not used. I think this helped the berries "stay afloat." The trick to cooking w/ Splenda and lower fat is to reduce baking temp. I baked this @ 350 deg. using my speed bake setting on my oven. It took 30 min. I was very pleased w/ the taste and texture. Plus it was a great way to use up the last of my blueberries from last summer! My husband also liked the reduced fat/sugar version.

