A friend served this with lemon verbena whipped cream, which was a terrific addition! Bring 1/4 c. whipping cream, 3 Tbs fresh lemon verbena (don't even need to chop it), and 2 Tbs. sugar just to a simmer. While this is cooling in the fridge, whip 2 c. cream to soft peaks. Strain the cooled verbena mixture, add to the rest of the cream and finish whipping. Just lovely - brought a nice contrast to the berries.

