This is the "scratch" version of a "pudding" my mom has made for 50 years with sweetened bisquick. The trick is to take the fruit and juice to a simmer before pouring it over the dough. Then the fruit sinks thru the dough and makes a delectable squidgy fruit jam at the bottom of the pan. Mom always used a 9x13 pan and a quart of fruit and juice. I beg for it every time I go home.

