This is a great, easy, and rustic recipe, and I can imagine it used with lots of different fresh berry ingredients! We are currently "between berries" in our local growing season, so I had to use canned blueberries (drained and rinsed). This did not mar the recipe's success: they sunk as the batter rose during baking. Next time, I'll add lemon peel and Chambord (black raspberry liqueur) to the mix, as suggested by another reviewer. To those who seem disappointed that this didn't turn out like a pudding, I challenge them to explore the wider world of puddings beyond bland egg and milk dessert custards. For example, the British call a baked batter of flour, milk and eggs, with the addition of meat drippings a "Yorkshire pudding."

