This was easy to make and worked perfectly for me in an 8X8 square glass baking dish. My husband loved it warm with vanilla ice cream. The berries did not sink when I poured the berry mix on the batter (recipe led me to think they would sink immediately for some reason) however the cake rose and the berries sank during cooking and it turned out perfectly. It has a very airy consistency and would be a superb dish for a dessert at a buffet supper or dinner party. It also microwaves well to warm it up again. I will definitely make again and recommend to friends...It is one of those dishes that is easy to make but it seems quite special and different...

Rating: 3
This is a very simple cake that is perfect for breakfast or a picnic. I have made it twice, using different sized pans to see the effect. In an 8 inch square glass dish you will get a core of blueberry that is tasty but not very pretty for guests. Using a 9 inch round glass dish I got a more presentable cake but less pudding like consistency and more suitable for breakfast than dessert.

Rating: 4
Maybe the batter was too thick on the first reviewers cake, but this was absolutely perfect when we made it last night. Our guests ate seconds and my office this morning ate the rest for breakfast. Set up beautifully and has many layers of blueberries and cake. Fantastic! To the first reviewer, try it again, it's worth it!

Rating: 2
This was extremely simple to prepare but very disappionting in appearance. My blueberry mixture did not "sink" as described. The surface had a violet discoloration and not the golden and blue contrast as photographed. It tasted fine, not great. There wasn't any component that could be construed as "pudding". I followed the instructions exactly and made no substitutions.